  "verdict": "Tidal admittance reproduces |s_N| to 1.6e-03 (small-eps) and the 2f/1f harmonic ratio matches the analytic curvature law to 5.5e-02, rising from 0.013 (well-grounded) to 0.100 near flotation. Tides-only inversion recovers the flotation-proximity R to 3.1% and m to 0.0% from velocity alone. So ocean tides are a continuous, self-calibrating third probe of the same sliding law and an operational ungrounding early-warning (R(t)->1)."
